1
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:00,962
Frieren.

2
00:02:08,594 --> 00:02:10,055
The royal capital's in sight.

3
00:02:10,656 --> 00:02:13,319
They're celebrating the
triumphant return of their heroes.

4
00:02:13,659 --> 00:02:15,160
I can feel the excitement from here.

5
00:02:18,143 --> 00:02:20,045
We'll have to start looking for work soon.

6
00:02:20,966 --> 00:02:23,048
You're already concerned about employment?

7
00:02:23,629 --> 00:02:24,629
As we all should be.

8
00:02:25,290 --> 00:02:27,833
Slaying the Demon King
was one chapter, but read on.

9
00:02:28,979 --> 00:02:31,521
For we've stories yet to
tell and lives yet to live.

10
00:02:32,042 --> 00:02:33,103
Life's full of work.

11
00:02:33,963 --> 00:02:35,965
I would take any job they let me drink on.

12
00:02:36,546 --> 00:02:37,767
Very priestly, sir.

13
00:02:40,429 --> 00:02:41,429
I suppose you're right.

14
00:02:44,253 --> 00:02:51,459
Frieren, the life that lies ahead of you will be far longer than
the rest of us could know or that we could begin to comprehend.

15
00:02:52,460 --> 00:02:53,460
Yes, perhaps.

16
00:03:31,039 --> 00:03:38,322
Himmel, the Hero, Eisen, the Warrior,
Heiter, the Priest, and Frieren, the Mage.

17
00:03:39,602 --> 00:03:42,623
You have our wholehearted
thanks for defeating the Demon King.

18
00:03:43,023 --> 00:03:47,585
Your efforts have launched our world
into an age of prosperity and peace.

19
00:04:03,297 --> 00:04:06,699
Rumor has it that the king is going
to erect statues of us in the plaza.

20
00:04:07,619 --> 00:04:12,242
Though, I doubt they'll be able to capture the
complexities of my good looks in a piece of stone.

21
00:04:12,542 --> 00:04:14,063
How I pity the poor sculptor.

22
00:04:15,203 --> 00:04:16,644
It's a self-serving tribute.

23
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:20,126
When we left, he was only
willing to offer up ten copper coins.

24
00:04:22,297 --> 00:04:23,838
Oh, don't keep your head in the past.

25
00:04:24,198 --> 00:04:26,599
Tonight, the gallant
adventurers drink for free.

26
00:04:26,999 --> 00:04:28,920
I would say that makes
us even, wouldn't you?

27
00:04:29,380 --> 00:04:30,821
I'm not a corrupt priest.

28
00:04:32,101 --> 00:04:39,905
It's over, isn't it?

29
00:04:41,246 --> 00:04:42,246
Indeed.

30
00:04:43,186 --> 00:04:45,387
This is the moment our
grand adventure ends.

31
00:04:46,668 --> 00:04:47,808
Ten years together.

32
00:04:48,549 --> 00:04:50,910
We've been through the
thick, the thin, and then some.

33
00:04:52,332 --> 00:04:58,498
The day we departed, Himmel and Eisen's disrespect
toward the king landed the moments away from execution.

34
00:04:58,998 --> 00:05:01,038
One misstep and our journey
would have ended there.

35
00:05:02,942 --> 00:05:06,004
Do you remember the time Heiter's
bottle-ache rendered him all but useless?

36
00:05:11,109 --> 00:05:13,351
You've gone nearly as pallid as an undead.

37
00:05:13,531 --> 00:05:14,531
Are you passing?

38
00:05:15,293 --> 00:05:16,534
Alas, a shame indeed.

39
00:05:17,515 --> 00:05:19,197
That was a weakly occurrence.

40
00:05:19,657 --> 00:05:21,535
Well, I was exceptional in every way.

41
00:05:21,559 --> 00:05:25,323
We debated leaving you behind
when you fell for that mimic, you know.

42
00:05:25,523 --> 00:05:28,126
We repeatedly told her it was
a trap, and yet here we are.

43
00:05:28,426 --> 00:05:29,847
Is it time to lose the elf?

44
00:05:35,013 --> 00:05:38,396
Looking back, our memories
sound terrible, don't they?

45
00:05:40,065 --> 00:05:41,065
But I had fun.

46
00:05:41,987 --> 00:05:44,069
You made this quest
the journey of my lifetime.

47
00:05:44,369 --> 00:05:45,369
Thank you all.

48
00:05:46,131 --> 00:05:47,131
I feel the same way.

49
00:05:47,793 --> 00:05:49,651
Our adventure was a mere ten years.

50
00:05:49,675 --> 00:05:51,377
A mere ten?

51
00:05:51,757 --> 00:05:52,858
But that's a full decade.

52
00:05:53,178 --> 00:05:54,179
Spent on one job.

53
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:55,500
I mean, look at Heiter.

54
00:05:55,741 --> 00:05:57,983
He's turned into an old
man right before our eyes.

55
00:05:58,203 --> 00:05:59,203
That's not nice.

56
00:05:59,825 --> 00:06:00,986
He always looked like that.

57
00:06:01,567 --> 00:06:02,567
Even less nice.

58
00:06:09,812 --> 00:06:10,852
It's nearly time.

59
00:06:19,456 --> 00:06:20,796
We're here on a special night.

60
00:06:21,016 --> 00:06:22,016
How enchanting.

61
00:06:22,697 --> 00:06:25,498
The era meteor shower
happens once every 50 years.

62
00:06:26,778 --> 00:06:29,639
Our era of peace can be
welcomed in a more perfect way.

63
00:06:32,921 --> 00:06:33,921
Beautiful.

64
00:06:34,061 --> 00:06:36,082
The view from inside
the city isn't very good.

65
00:06:36,842 --> 00:06:38,202
I'm trying to have a moment here.

66
00:06:38,643 --> 00:06:39,643
Don't spoil the mood.

67
00:06:42,161 --> 00:06:43,161
Next time then.

68
00:06:45,102 --> 00:06:46,102
I know a good place.

69
00:06:46,482 --> 00:06:49,383
I'll take us there when the
opportunity arises in 50 years.

70
00:06:53,124 --> 00:06:54,124
What's wrong?

71
00:06:54,445 --> 00:06:55,445
Nothing.

72
00:06:55,725 --> 00:06:56,725
Nothing in the world.

73
00:06:58,766 --> 00:06:59,766
So it's a plan.

74
00:07:00,507 --> 00:07:01,507
50 years from now.

75
00:07:24,622 --> 00:07:25,903
I suppose I should be leaving.

76
00:07:26,804 --> 00:07:28,265
Mapped out your next adventure?

77
00:07:28,885 --> 00:07:30,987
For the next 100 years, give or take.

78
00:07:31,448 --> 00:07:34,370
I intend to travel around the
Central Lands collecting new spells.

79
00:07:35,070 --> 00:07:36,512
Well, I'll be sure to stop by.

80
00:07:42,496 --> 00:07:44,878
The way elves see this world is a mystery.

81
00:07:45,138 --> 00:07:47,380
Who knows how long she's
been a part of it by now.

82
00:07:48,741 --> 00:07:53,305
In her eyes, 50 or even 100
years must look like a trifling thing.

83
00:08:44,556 --> 00:08:45,736
Shadow Dragon horns?

84
00:08:46,596 --> 00:08:48,797
I'm afraid we don't have
anything like that here.

85
00:08:49,117 --> 00:08:52,458
The last time I saw a Shadow Dragon
must have been a few decades ago.

86
00:08:53,298 --> 00:08:54,878
Ah, how unfortunate.

87
00:08:55,418 --> 00:08:56,759
I needed one for summoning.

88
00:08:59,819 --> 00:09:02,900
Come to think of it, I took a horn
from the Demon King's castle.

89
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:04,740
I asked Himmel to store it.

90
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:08,981
You do see that it's exuding
some sort of evil aura, don't you?

91
00:09:09,241 --> 00:09:10,621
Is that dangerous to people?

92
00:09:10,901 --> 00:09:11,901
Uh, I don't know.

93
00:09:12,242 --> 00:09:13,518
That's awfully reassuring.

94
00:09:13,542 --> 00:09:17,143
The Aera Meteor Shower
should be circling around soon.

95
00:09:17,503 --> 00:09:18,903
I'll pick up the horn when I visit.

96
00:09:25,215 --> 00:09:27,896
The city's changed a fair
bit since I was here last.

97
00:09:42,923 --> 00:09:46,364
It should be somewhere
around here... Frieren?

98
00:09:47,705 --> 00:09:48,705
Himmel, is that...

99
00:09:55,610 --> 00:09:56,811
You're near ancient!

100
00:09:57,071 --> 00:09:58,291
Must you be so blunt?

101
00:10:00,952 --> 00:10:04,294
Considering my advanced age,
I'm still quite handsome, yes?

102
00:10:06,234 --> 00:10:10,896
Hard to believe it's been so long, when you
show up looking the same as the day we met.

103
00:10:12,177 --> 00:10:14,458
I'd convinced myself I
would never see you again.

104
00:10:17,759 --> 00:10:19,200
The Era Meteor Shower.

105
00:10:19,900 --> 00:10:21,021
Such fond memories.

106
00:10:21,821 --> 00:10:24,542
About the item we looted
from the Demon King's castle.

107
00:10:24,827 --> 00:10:30,090
If you're referring to the Shadow Dragon Horn, I've
thought about that blasted thing every day since you left.

108
00:10:30,730 --> 00:10:33,871
My cabinet has been exuding
an evil aura for decades now.

109
00:10:34,672 --> 00:10:35,692
Sorry, I think.

110
00:10:36,573 --> 00:10:39,814
Though you do know you could have stashed
it in a shed or something of the like.

111
00:10:41,435 --> 00:10:42,435
I couldn't do that.

112
00:10:47,358 --> 00:10:51,400
I realize you may not have thought much of
leaving your ominous prize under my care.

113
00:10:52,104 --> 00:10:56,827
But in my eyes, this horn was a treasure
entrusted to me by a dear friend for safekeeping.

114
00:10:57,707 --> 00:11:00,849
I had to keep it in perfect
condition until I could return it to you.

115
00:11:09,914 --> 00:11:12,535
It's truly nothing greater
than a convenient ingredient.

116
00:11:32,638 --> 00:11:33,840
What's taking so long?

117
00:11:34,741 --> 00:11:36,843
You don't exactly have
any hair to fuss over.

118
00:11:37,985 --> 00:11:40,067
We bald men have our particularities.

119
00:11:48,017 --> 00:11:49,017
Quickly now.

120
00:11:49,058 --> 00:11:51,341
The meteor shower
won't wait for man nor elf.

121
00:11:59,684 --> 00:12:01,605
You've grown rather dignified, Heiter.

122
00:12:02,005 --> 00:12:04,205
As a bishop of the Holy City, must.

123
00:12:04,905 --> 00:12:07,262
I'd return the compliment,
but change evades you.

124
00:12:07,286 --> 00:12:09,563
Guess my head's still not for padding.

125
00:12:09,587 --> 00:12:13,548
At least you're much
the same as ever, Eisen.

126
00:12:14,308 --> 00:12:16,189
Fanny, is that how I seem?

127
00:12:16,549 --> 00:12:18,089
You are a dwarf, after all.

128
00:12:18,429 --> 00:12:21,070
Where is this place of
meteor-viewing miracles?

129
00:12:22,230 --> 00:12:23,751
We're headed there so soon.

130
00:12:24,111 --> 00:12:28,492
Isn't it a little ridiculous to stake
our claim to a spot so far in advance?

131
00:12:28,973 --> 00:12:31,634
Well, for our spot is
about a week's walk away.

132
00:12:32,874 --> 00:12:34,531
To what have I agreed?

133
00:12:34,555 --> 00:12:35,975
What a shame.

134
00:12:36,416 --> 00:12:38,716
You should have learned to
respect your elders by now.

135
00:12:42,638 --> 00:12:44,098
This brings back memories.

136
00:12:45,739 --> 00:12:46,739
Traveling together.

137
00:12:48,460 --> 00:12:50,856
It transports the soul to a different time.

138
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:55,042
A time when the world was ours to discover.

139
00:12:56,567 --> 00:13:01,723
And each mark of life on its
surface seems so brilliant and new.

140
00:13:26,182 --> 00:13:32,607
As I brush the dust off each memory,
there you all appear, right behind my eyes.

141
00:13:34,569 --> 00:13:39,333
I have lived my life, waiting for the day
that we would be together once more.

142
00:13:40,674 --> 00:13:41,855
I thank you, Frieren.

143
00:13:43,416 --> 00:13:48,200
It's solely because of you that this
retired hero could have one final adventure.

144
00:14:13,573 --> 00:14:14,573
Beautiful.

145
00:14:41,577 --> 00:14:44,699
Though he's gone, I do believe
he was happy when he left.

146
00:14:44,739 --> 00:14:47,560
I'm not sure.

147
00:14:55,324 --> 00:14:57,405
That girl was one of Himmel's companions.

148
00:14:58,326 --> 00:15:00,127
I've yet to even see her frown.

149
00:15:00,967 --> 00:15:02,048
How heartless.

150
00:15:03,608 --> 00:15:04,970
Oh, be fair, ladies.

151
00:15:05,331 --> 00:15:07,194
Not like we're racked with grief either.

152
00:15:07,394 --> 00:15:10,580
Show some respect for
yourself, you know, Hort!

153
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:11,902
How am I to know?

154
00:15:37,348 --> 00:15:40,832
In all truthfulness, I hardly
knew anything about him.

155
00:15:53,684 --> 00:15:57,108
Ten years with him wasn't
nearly enough time to learn.

156
00:16:04,810 --> 00:16:12,810
I was aware that human lives are short, but this... Why
didn't I try to... try to better know and understand you?

157
00:16:24,830 --> 00:16:26,572
My head is still not for padding.

158
00:16:34,815 --> 00:16:37,736
The Holy City calls, and
I shan't make them wait.

159
00:16:41,238 --> 00:16:43,659
Before I go, let me get a good look.

160
00:16:44,460 --> 00:16:46,701
This will likely be the
last time that I see you.

161
00:16:47,181 --> 00:16:48,222
Why, are you unwell?

162
00:16:48,622 --> 00:16:51,283
My years of drinking had to
catch up with me at some point.

163
00:16:51,443 --> 00:16:52,784
Divine retribution.

164
00:16:54,425 --> 00:16:59,167
If either of you find yourselves in the
Holy City, offer me a bottle at my grave.

165
00:17:00,948 --> 00:17:03,229
Does the thought of dying
not cause you any fear?

166
00:17:06,020 --> 00:17:08,902
We're the party of adventurers
that saved the world.

167
00:17:09,622 --> 00:17:12,864
I'd like to think our seats in
heaven have long been reserved.

168
00:17:13,965 --> 00:17:17,687
That's the whole reason I fought
alongside you ruffians in the first place.

169
00:17:18,007 --> 00:17:19,268
You corrupt priest.

170
00:17:22,010 --> 00:17:23,310
If you'll kindly excuse me.

171
00:17:31,855 --> 00:17:34,397
Well, I should be on the road then, too.

172
00:17:35,719 --> 00:17:37,260
Off to collect more spells?

173
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:39,720
There's that.

174
00:17:40,521 --> 00:17:43,102
But I also wish to learn
more about humankind.

175
00:17:45,463 --> 00:17:46,463
Do you now?

176
00:17:47,783 --> 00:17:49,664
Speaking of, I've a proposition for you.

177
00:17:50,084 --> 00:17:54,546
Though a mage is quite powerful, she could
be doubly so with a warrior by her side.

178
00:17:55,046 --> 00:17:56,167
Give me a break.

179
00:17:57,087 --> 00:17:59,668
I'm far too old to swing an axe these days.

180
00:18:03,503 --> 00:18:05,724
Don't make that face at me, Frieren.

181
00:18:06,524 --> 00:18:12,386
Once you've lost your vigor, your body
slows, and your life must slow with it.

182
00:18:13,246 --> 00:18:14,246
I see.

183
00:18:14,767 --> 00:18:16,187
We'll meet again someday, Eisen.

184
00:18:17,587 --> 00:18:18,587
Sure.

185
00:18:18,628 --> 00:18:19,628
Someday.

186
00:18:34,579 --> 00:18:35,579
Dramaturg, Dramaturg.

187
00:19:00,662 --> 00:19:02,143
I saw that tree earlier.

188
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:04,644
These woods are always quite the labyrinth.

189
00:19:05,825 --> 00:19:06,825
Where am I?

190
00:19:11,308 --> 00:19:12,829
You seem a bit lost, ma'am.

191
00:19:18,492 --> 00:19:20,113
Is there something you're looking for?

192
00:19:21,133 --> 00:19:21,474
Yes.

193
00:19:21,874 --> 00:19:24,511
I'm trying to locate the
home of a man named Heiter.

194
00:19:24,535 --> 00:19:25,896
I see.

195
00:19:26,156 --> 00:19:27,156
So you're a visitor.

196
00:19:30,662 --> 00:19:32,603
The corrupt priest is slow to die.

197
00:19:34,344 --> 00:19:37,886
Turns out a stylish exit is
harder to achieve than I thought.

198
00:19:38,487 --> 00:19:40,708
I brought some liquor
to offer at your grave.

199
00:19:41,268 --> 00:19:42,369
Would you like a drink?

200
00:19:43,069 --> 00:19:45,290
I gave the stuff up.

201
00:19:46,691 --> 00:19:48,292
I doubt the goddess will forgive you.

202
00:19:48,592 --> 00:19:51,274
You're far too close to corpse
hood to clean up your act now.

203
00:19:51,914 --> 00:19:59,914
Why, thank you, kind lady.

204
00:20:05,942 --> 00:20:06,942
Who is she?

205
00:20:07,203 --> 00:20:08,283
Her name is Fern.

206
00:20:09,064 --> 00:20:11,865
She was orphaned by the
wars in the southern lands.

207
00:20:13,186 --> 00:20:14,506
My, how unexpected.

208
00:20:15,067 --> 00:20:18,128
I never thought you the type
to do charity for charity's sake.

209
00:20:18,688 --> 00:20:19,809
That was always Himmel.

210
00:20:23,051 --> 00:20:25,452
Frieren, why did you come visit me?

211
00:20:26,192 --> 00:20:31,935
I had a few errands to run in the Holy City, and I want to
learn more about those I have met and will meet on my travels.

212
00:20:33,495 --> 00:20:36,157
You've done me much good,
so I came here to repay my debts.

213
00:20:36,597 --> 00:20:38,238
I imagine your time is running low.

214
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:43,941
In that case, I have a request.

215
00:20:45,462 --> 00:20:47,083
Might you take on an apprentice?

216
00:20:49,244 --> 00:20:52,866
Fern has potential as a mage,
but needs adequate training.

217
00:20:53,286 --> 00:20:55,868
Will you bring her with you
and strengthen her skills?

218
00:20:59,394 --> 00:21:02,095
Forgive me, Heiter, but I must draw a line.

219
00:21:03,076 --> 00:21:04,196
She'd only get in my way.

220
00:21:05,497 --> 00:21:08,499
We both know how often
apprentice mages die in battle.

221
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:13,441
I will not send a child my friend
asked me to care for to her death.

222
00:21:17,143 --> 00:21:17,719
Understood.

223
00:21:17,743 --> 00:21:20,785
I have another favor in mind.

224
00:21:26,060 --> 00:21:29,061
This was unearthed from
the tomb of Evig the Sage.

225
00:21:29,722 --> 00:21:37,465
Inside this grimoire, there is said to be a wealth of lost
spells with powers ranging from resurrection to immortality.

226
00:21:37,905 --> 00:21:40,607
I find it hard to believe
that such magic exists.

227
00:21:41,707 --> 00:21:44,668
That's part of the reason
why I'd like you to decipher it.

228
00:21:45,549 --> 00:21:46,549
Up for the challenge?

229
00:21:47,110 --> 00:21:49,050
The code is largely symbol-based.

230
00:21:49,411 --> 00:21:51,932
The people of this era had
a penchant for such things.

231
00:21:52,832 --> 00:21:54,473
I'll need at least five or six years.

232
00:21:55,827 --> 00:21:56,827
Do what you can.

233
00:21:57,849 --> 00:22:00,310
Why do you want these spells
deciphered in the first place?

234
00:22:00,991 --> 00:22:02,972
You told us that death doesn't worry you.

235
00:22:03,693 --> 00:22:10,518
When I said I wasn't afraid to die, I may have been more
concerned with my perceived courage than the truth of my words.

236
00:22:11,339 --> 00:22:14,781
More than that, my fear has
grown since we spoke on the matter.

237
00:22:16,242 --> 00:22:21,946
And even if immortality is out of
my grasp, I'm not ready to go just yet.

238
00:22:22,207 --> 00:22:23,968
I'll take any more time that I can.

239
00:22:28,339 --> 00:22:32,220
If you read the holy texts, you'll
find instructions to live a healthy life.

240
00:22:32,460 --> 00:22:35,161
What better expression of
health than a few more years?

241
00:22:35,641 --> 00:22:37,041
Miscreant of the cloth.

242
00:22:39,742 --> 00:22:46,283
Oh, and whenever you need a break from your task, do
you mind teaching Fern the magic that you see fit?

243
00:22:46,943 --> 00:22:51,284
As a priest, I lack the knowledge
to further her studies in Magery.

244
00:22:51,985 --> 00:22:53,705
All right, that should be fine.

245
00:23:02,135 --> 00:23:03,135
There you are.

246
00:23:04,436 --> 00:23:06,416
I could scarcely find any trace of you.

247
00:23:06,896 --> 00:23:08,796
Are the woods your usual training grounds?

248
00:23:09,257 --> 00:23:13,458
I know I can be hard to find, but I didn't think
someone like you would have that same trouble.

249
00:23:13,898 --> 00:23:15,858
Master Heiter never knows where I am.

250
00:23:16,298 --> 00:23:18,019
He says I'm practically invisible.

251
00:23:20,059 --> 00:23:22,099
I think that is a very
good thing, don't you?

252
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:24,960
Tis indeed.

253
00:23:28,046 --> 00:23:29,046
It's true.

254
00:23:29,768 --> 00:23:31,469
I can barely detect her presence.

255
00:23:32,470 --> 00:23:34,812
Her control over her mana is exceptional.

256
00:23:36,074 --> 00:23:38,496
How much could she have
studied at such a young age?

257
00:23:39,977 --> 00:23:45,463
Master Heiter said, once I'm able to blast
a hole in that rock, I'll be a proper mage.

258
00:23:46,243 --> 00:23:46,443
Huh.

259
00:23:47,264 --> 00:23:48,585
His idea is a decent one.

260
00:23:49,026 --> 00:23:50,026
That's a.

261
00:23:55,985 --> 00:23:58,206
My magic never makes it to the other side.

262
00:23:58,586 --> 00:23:59,586
It just won't reach.

263
00:24:00,787 --> 00:24:01,787
I see the issue.

264
00:24:02,388 --> 00:24:04,469
Do you know any ways
I can train this skill?

265
00:24:05,949 --> 00:24:08,190
Yes, but can I ask you something first?

266
00:24:09,671 --> 00:24:10,712
Do you like magic?

267
00:24:11,712 --> 00:24:13,173
I like it somewhat, I guess.

268
00:24:16,254 --> 00:24:17,415
In that, we're alike.

